{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "# Q: 403 on cloudaicompanion API: preview models inaccessible despite admin enabling Preview Release Channel\n**Source:** https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/issues/23826\n\n## The Problem / Request\n## Summary\n\nGemini CLI returns a 403/404 error when attempting to use preview models (e.g. `gemini-3-flash-preview`), even though the Google Workspace admin has enabled the Preview Release Channel for the organization. **Stable models (e.g. `gemini-2.5-flash`) work fine.**\n\n## Environment\n\n- Gemini CLI version: 0.35.0\n- OS: macOS (Darwin 25.3.0)\n- Auth type: `oauth-personal`\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Admin enables Preview Release Channel in Google Admin Console \u2192 Apps \u2192 Additional Google services \u2192 Gemini Code Assist \u2192 Settings\n2. User runs `gemini auth login` with Google Workspace account\n3. User starts a session with `gemini --model gemini-3-flash-preview`\n4. User sends any message\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nPreview models should be available since the admin has enabled the Preview Release Channel.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nTwo different errors depending on path:\n\n**When selecting preview model via UI:** The CLI shows:\n```\nIt seems like you don't have access to gemini-3-flash-preview.\nYour admin might have disabled the access. Contact them to enable the Preview Release Channel.\n```\n\n**When forcing via `--model gemini-3-flash-preview`:** 403 permission denied:\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": 403,\n    \"message\": \"Permission 'cloudaicompanion.companions.generateChat' denied on resource '//cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/projects/<auto-provisioned-project>/locations/global' (or it may not exist).\",\n    \"status\": \"PERMISSION_DENIED\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nOr 404 ModelNotFoundError when the CLI silently downgrades to a stable model but still fails.\n\n## Key Finding\n\n- **Stable models work** (`gemini-2.5-flash`, `gemini-2.5-pro`) \u2014 no 