{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "(`gemini-2.5-flash`, `gemini-2.5-pro`) \u2014 no issues.\n- **Preview models fail** (`gemini-3-flash-preview`, `gemini-3-pro-preview`) \u2014 403/404.\n- The admin has confirmed the Preview Release Channel is enabled in Google Admin Console.\n- The error references an auto-provisioned GCP project that the user did not configure.\n- The same error occurs with a completely different personal Gmail account (not in the Workspace org).\n- The project ID is not cached locally in `~/.gemini/` \u2014 it is resolved server-side.\n- Removing ADC credentials does not resolve the issue.\n\n## The Solution / Discussion\n### Response 1\nFound possible duplicate issues:\n\n- #23103\n- #21005\n\nIf you believe this is not a duplicate, please remove the `status/possible-duplicate` label.\n<!-- gemini-cli-deduplication -->\n\n### Response 2\nResolved \u2014 root cause was a stale `GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT_ID` environment variable in `~/.zshrc` that Gemini CLI was picking up as the project for API calls. Removing it fixed the issue. Not a Gemini CLI bug.\n\n", "timestamp": null, "embedding": [0.6382492184638977, 0.7831876873970032, -2.595045804977417, -0.8498408198356628, 1.531701683998108, -0.03591368719935417, 0.2634928226470947, -0.34105443954467773, -0.2693813741207123, -0.28227269649505615, -0.9060927033424377, 1.0992506742477417, 0.5810806751251221, 0.4076617360115051, -0.15818220376968384, -0.006565996445715427, 1.206488013267517, -0.6784781813621521, -0.5203250050544739, 1.0522109270095825, -0.3214801251888275, -1.0177021026611328, 0.38393211364746094, -0.2983362674713135, 2.218174695968628, 1.3030312061309814, 0.9582425951957703, 0.3480057418346405, 0.05871438980102539, -0.42783498764038086, 1.5891761779785156, -0.3379381597042084, -0.5328973531723022, -0.7188486456871033, -0.4888506233692169, -0.6001893877983093, 0.5636748671531677, -0.5536714792251587, -0.707427442073822, 0.5735141038894653, 0.3328154087066650